<HEAD>Art Dealer, Son Of Painter, Dead At 79</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NICE, France (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Pierre Matisse, an art dealer who devoted
his career to promoting the works of such contemporary masters as
Chagall, Miro, Balthus, Dubuffet and Giacometti, has died at age 79.
   Matisse, son of the painter Henri Matisse, died Wednesday at the
Princess Grace Hospital in Monaco, not far from his home in St.
Jean-Cap Ferrat, France, hospital officials said. The cause of
death was not disclosed.
   Matisse owned galleries in New York and France and was known as
an authority on 20th century art.
   He is survived by his wife, Marie Gaetana von Spreti, a
daughter, Jacqueline Monnier, and two sons, Paul and Pierre-Noel.
   Funeral services were planned for Monday at the church in St.
Jean-Cap Ferrat.
