<SECOND>AM-People-Linkletter,0141</SECOND>
<HEAD>Radio, TV Host Art Linkletter Should Be Out of Hospital Soon</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Broadcast personality Art Linkletter is
expected to get out of the hospital next week after treatment for
high blood pressure, a UCLA Medical Center spokesman said Friday.
   Linkletter, 77, entered the hospital Wednesday night,
complaining of chest pains. He was resting comfortably and in good
condition in the cardiac care unit, hospital spokesman Rich Elbaum
said.
   ``He did not suffer a heart attack, and he is now being treated
for high blood pressure,'' hospital spokesman Rich Elbaum said.
``He is awake, alert and talking. He is expected to leave the
hospital sometime next week.''
   Linkletter was host of television and radio shows for decades
and wrote the best-sellers ``Kids Say the Darndest Things'' and
``Old Age is Not for Sissies.''
</TEXT>
