<HEAD>Soviet-Israeli Joint Venture Founded to Make Medical Equipment</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MOSCOW (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The first Soviet-Israeli joint economic venture
will manufacture medical diagnostic equipment in Kiev, Tass
announced.
   Relations between Israel and the Soviet Union have been growing
warmer in recent months, but full diplomatic ties have not been
restored. The Soviet Union broke off relations with Israel in 1967.
   Tass quoted Andrei Serdyuk, deputy health minister in the
Ukraine, as saying the joint venture was formed by his ministry,
the Israeli corporation Elscint and a Kiev weapons manufacturing
plant starting to make goods for the consumer sector.
