<FIRST>u i AM-Portugal-TWA     08-11 0146</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Portugal-TWA,0150</SECOND>
<HEAD>TWA Jetliner Has Engine Problem, Returns to Lisbon</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LISBON, Portugal (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A TWA jetliner en route to New York from
Lison with about 360 passengers aboard developed engine trouble and
returned to Lisbon's Portella Airport Friday, landing without
incident, airport officials reported.
   They said the airport's emergency services were placed on full
alert. An air traffic control officer said the pilot of the Boeing
747 made a perfect landing, and Lisbon news reports said no one was
injured..
   TWA spokesman Don Morrison said in St. Louis that the ``No. 1
engine shut down. Compressor stall was the cause. They're checking
the engine out now.'' He said the four-engine jetliner was in the
air 63 minutes.
   ``There was no emergency declared. He (the pilot) did not make
an emergency landing,'' Morrison said.
   Morrison said he had no exact figure for the number aboard.
</TEXT>
