<FIRST>r i AM-Morocco-Polisario     08-11 0200</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Morocco-Polisario,0204</SECOND>
<HEAD>Senior Polisario Figure Defects to Morocco</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CASABLANCA, Morocco (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The North American representative of
the Polisario Front guerrilla group has defected to Morocco, the
official MAP news agency reported.
   Omar Hadrami, a leading member of the group fighting for the
independence of the Western Sahara, arrived in Casablanca on
Wednesday in response to a call from King Hassan II for Polisario
members to give up their struggle, MAP said.
   Hadrami, 40, was based in New York. He was one of the 25 members
of the Polisario's Political Bureau.
   No immediate comment came from the organization, which is based
in neighboring Algeria.
   In a speech Nov. 6, Hassan called on all Polisario members
``with a drop of Moroccan blood in their veins'' to change sides in
a struggle that has lasted nearly 15 years. ``The motherland is
merciful and compassionate,'' the king said.
   The Polisario Front has been waging a desert battle against
Moroccan soldiers since the North African country annexed the
territory, the former Spanish Sahara, in 1975. Military action has
been at a virtual standstill for months as the United Nations tries
to mediate between the two sides, trying for a referendum in the
territory.
</TEXT>
