<HEAD>Northwest Airlines Pilots Resume Contract Talks</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MINNEAPOLIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Talks resumed today between Northwest
Airlines and the carrier's 5,000 pilots, a National Mediation Board
spokesman said.
   William A. Gill Jr., assistant executive director of the
mediation board, said the location of the talks would not be
disclosed.
   Talks between the two sides broke off a couple weeks ago when
the pilots requested an impasse. If the mediation board approves
that request, the pilots would be free to strike after a 30-day
cooling-off period.
   But Gill said no rulings have been made. He told The Associated
Press that the board encouraged the two sides to sit down again and
discuss their differences.
   The pilots' union and the company did not immediately return
phone calls today.
</TEXT>
