<HEAD>London Shares End Higher</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Share prices closed higher on Friday after a late
rally inspired by the release of U.S. economic data that pointed to
a slowing of the U.S. economy.
   The U.S. producer price index and retail sales figures for July
prompted a strong rally in U.S. stocks and bonds, though Wall
Street started dropping from its early peaks as trading wound up in
London.
   Despite the late rally, nearly half the top 100 stocks showed
price losses at the close.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index closed 6.9
points, or 0.3 percent, higher at 2,354.2.
   The Financial Times 30-share index closed 8.2 points higher at
1,969.6. The Financial Times 500-share index rose 3.21 points to
close at 1,326.14.
   Volume was 605.8 million shares, up from 574.5 million shares on
Thursday.
